# Marathon — Project Guide

## The Book

Historical fiction set in Athens, 514–490 BCE. Pheidippides is the legendary runner who ran to Sparta and back before the Battle of Marathon — and then, according to legend, ran 26 miles to announce victory and died.

In our version, he's secretly the illegitimate son of Hipparchus (the tyrant's brother, killed when Pheidippides was a child). He doesn't know this. The novel follows a *nothos* — a bastard excluded from the democracy he'll die to save — who runs to prove he belongs, and discovers he's the son of everything democracy was built to destroy.

